\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 Dorm Seven's dining table\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 usually home to dust and the occasional forgotten textbook\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 gleamed under an uncharacteristic arrangement of chipped plates and mismatched cutlery. Henry kept adjusting the placement of a fork, his dorm captain instincts warring with disbelief that his residents were actually using the common area for its intended purpose.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Christine's teacup hovered halfway to her lips, her usual aristocratic poise shattered as she stared openly at Catherine. The morning light caught the elf's sharp cheekbones and the subtle points of her ears, making her seem more like a storybook illustration than a being of flesh and blood.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 "You're... you're really one of them," Christine breathed, her voice uncharacteristically small. "The Fair Folk of the Silver Courts."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Catherine's smirk deepened as she drizzled honey over a pancake with theatrical flair. "Oh, we had many names. The Shining Bane. The Dawn Bringers. The Heartless Conquerors." She leaned forward, her eyes glinting. "Which bedtime stories did your nurses tell, little lordling?"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 A flush crept up Christine's neck. At her side, Geralt shifted protectively, his massive frame making the chair creak in protest.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Will snorted into his wine glass. "Careful, princess. She'll have you trading your firstborn for a pretty song."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 "Already got one of those, thanks," Catherine quipped, ruffling Eddie's hair as she passed. He batted her hand away with a grumble, but there was no real heat in it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Ashley, ever the diplomat, cleared her throat. "The pancakes are incredible, Catherine. Is this really what elven legionnaires ate?"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 "Only on good days," Catherine said, pouring more wine\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 into proper glasses now, much to Henry's visible relief. "Mostly we survived on hardtack and spite." She winked at Christine. "The 'fair lords and maidens' nonsense came later, when bards needed romantic endings."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Eddie watched as Christine carefully cut her pancake into perfect squares\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 a nervous habit he recognized from their academy days. The heiress who'd once mocked him for his "peasant magic" now sat starstruck before an actual mythical being. The irony wasn't lost on him.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 "So," Catherine's voice cut through the clatter of cutlery, her fingers steepled beneath her chin. "This rebellion of yours. Do you children actually intend to storm the Black Hand's underworld den?" Her tone walked the line between amusement and genuine concern.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Eddie set down his fork with deliberate calm. "We're going to try." He nudged a grease-stained notebook across the table\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 pages crammed with phone numbers, each crossed out after last night's desperate calls. "We've already started gathering others who've lost people."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Ashley leaned forward, her Campus Watch badge glinting beside a syrup smear. "There's a meeting tonight. Midnight at the Edenfield Archives." Her gaze locked onto Catherine's with uncharacteristic intensity. "You should come."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The room seemed to hold its breath. Even Christine stopped mutilating her breakfast.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Catherine swirled her wine, watching the legs slide down the glass. "The Archives," she mused. "Clever. No one would question students there after dark." A slow smile spread across her face. "Even if they're planning treason."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Henry choked on his coffee. "We're not\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 "}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 "Please," Catherine waved him off. "Storming a secret assassin stronghold? That's textbook treason." She took a satisfied sip before adding, "Deliciously so."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Will slammed his palms on the table, making the plates jump. "So you're in then?"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 All eyes turned to the elf. Outside, a gust of wind rattled the windows\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 or perhaps it was the university's ancient ghosts stirring in anticipation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Catherine's smile turned razor-sharp. "Well, I haven't committed proper treason since the Solivian Uprising." She topped up her wine glass with a flourish. "Wouldn't miss it for the world."}
